t the Null Route: 1. Debug Remnant: The ending may be a debug tool left by developers. The ELF header patterns and crash behavior suggest this is not a finished narrative element. 2. ARG Element: The ENDING_13_PTR reference and placeholder dialogue suggest an alternate reality game that requires solving puzzles outside the game client. 3. Cut True Ending: Some players believe this was the intended true ending before being cut during development. The map file and placeholder dialogue suggest a complete narrative was planned.\"}]]}]\n8:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\",\"children\":\"FAQ\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-on-surface-variant text-sm whitespace-pre-line\",\"children\":\"Q: Has anyone unlocked this legitimately? A: No. Despite six months of community attempts, no player has verified legitimate unlock conditions. Q: Can you trigger it through file editing? A: Yes, but this requires modifying save files and is not considered a legitimate unlock. The game crashes immediately after displaying hex data. Q: Is it related to the Corrupted Data ending? A: The community believes they are the same route, but this is unverified. The Corrupted Data ending may be what the Null Route was intended to unlock.\"}]]}]\n9:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\",\"children\":\"Related Content\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"href\":\"/endings/corrupted-data\",\"className\":\"bg-surface-container border border-outline/20 p-4 hover:border-primary transition-colors\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"font-[JetBrains_Mono] text-xs text-on-surface-variant mb-1\",\"children\":\"Related Ending\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-foreground\",\"children\":\"Corrupted Data →\"